case_circumstances: Unidentified white male at a missions facility in Muskogee OK. Complained of chest pain and collapsed.  He was transported to the hospital and eventually died.  The unidentified male did not have any identification with him and others at the mission did not know his name.  The victim had told others at the mission that he had been robbed while in Arkansas and had lost all of his belongings, including identification.  Possibly named "Gene / Jean."

case_facial_hair: Side burns extending to the earlobes
